pr_title: Added Dockerfiles for Linux and Mac
pr_body:
Running MARS in Linux requires us to create a new non-root user in Docker (otherwise the PDF and other files gets permission errors), which isn't required in Mac OS/X, so we now have 2 Dockerfiles in the `passive_user_input` directory. The script performs OS detection and uses the correct `Dockerfile` accordingly.
The Docker image building steps are also slightly different for Linux and Mac. This PR:
* Adds Dockerfiles for Linux and Mac to `passive_user_input`
* Modify shell script to auto-detect OS and select the right Dockerfile
* Add `output` directory and `.DS_Store` to `.gitignore`

Used `typo_fixer` scripts
Signed-off-by: ritik-malik <ritik18406@iiitd.ac.in>

Changed the metric file name to lower-case and with hyphen instead of underscore because :
1. The redirection from README.md was giving a 404
2. All other metrics are in lower-case, the [unofficial guide](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1chPzgJa49sO_f3wVqp_NLJupSVyKHSVyuFuwzl4m4KI/edit?pli=1#heading=h.4ejkic2mb7z1) also says the same

Signed-off-by: ritik-malik <ritik18406@iiitd.ac.in>

This PR fixes the following issues -

1. Replaced the dot-slash notation to focus-areas in the main [README](https://github.com/chaoss/wg-common/blob/master/README.md), to maintain the consistency across all Working Groups
2. The metrics directory was removed recently, but [CONTRIBUTING.md](https://github.com/chaoss/wg-common/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md) still contains stale link to it, replaced it with focus-areas link

This PR resolves the issue #114 

Removed the `template-folder`
Replicated the content of `file-name-convention.md` to chaoss/metrics and in the community-handbook

This PR addresses the issue of Standardizing READMEs for:
1. focus-areas/README.md
2. focus-areas/*\<focus-area>*/README.md

The issue can be found [here](https://github.com/chaoss/governance/issues/276), and the doc for template can be found [here](https://docs.google.com/document/d/12cac1TA_xTpUCcoTWg3e_03-m22CjLelTioaXRrTnpo/edit?usp=sharing)

Updates done:
* Added specific relative path format for pointing to the focus-areas as well as the metrics
* Added subheading in for each focus-area
* Reordered the focus-areas and metrics listed in the tables in lexicographical order to match the way github displays those files and folders

Signed-off-by: ritik-malik <ritik18406@iiitd.ac.in>

This PR marks the complete standardization of wg-common!
All the READMEs, focus-areas and metrics are now following the standard templates

Resloves #123 and #124 

The following changes have been made:
* Renamed `focus-areas` as discussed in the wg-common [meeting](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1xsii5tfmmDwWpuhrFcBJMeYeT3RipJdiCdHrbi0NalQ/edit#)
* Revised the new `focus-areas` goals and fixed the inconsistency
* Fixed links in the READMEs to accommodate new changes
* Fixed some metrics according to the newly modified [metrics template](https://github.com/chaoss/metrics/blob/master/resources/metrics-template.md)

Signed-off-by: ritik-malik <ritik18406@iiitd.ac.in>

I've added new directories for various metrics in the `focus-areas` directory,
for now I don't prefer to touch the old `metrics` directory` as it might be used by people for referring.

Also, I've downloaded the images which were hosted on `imgur` and referred in metrics, I added them to `images` dir.
I've not addressed the issue of naming conventions for metrics and their respective images. I plan to fix that in a different PR.

pr_title: renamed wg-common focus-areas and updated README
pr_body:
This PR is to rename the `focus-areas` in `wg-common` for Chinese translation and update the README.
It is based on the recent activity in [`wg-common`](https://github.com/chaoss/wg-common/tree/master/focus-areas) to rename all the focus-areas

Signed-off-by: ritik-malik <ritik18406@iiitd.ac.in>

The wg-common for Spanish translations is missing the `focus-areas` table and individual READMEs for each `focus-areas`.
Currently I've added them as per the English version as a placeholder. Each README contains a tag at the end that says -
> This README needs to be translated to Spanish

The metric markdowns are also modified according to the latest metric template.

Signed-off-by: ritik-malik <ritik18406@iiitd.ac.in>

The wg-risk for Spanish translations is missing the `focus-areas` table and individual READMEs for each focus-area.
Currently I've added them as per the English version as a placeholder. Each README contains a tag at the end that says -
> This README needs to be translated to Spanish

The metric markdowns are also modified according to the latest metric template.

Signed-off-by: ritik-malik <ritik18406@iiitd.ac.in>

This PR adds extra directory of `focus-areas` in wg-common and wg-risk for Spanish translations.
It helps us to:
1. Achieve standardization - the Chinese translations already have this structure
2. Easy implementation in MARS
